newsitem.title: USA: U.S. mortgage-backeds slip, stuck in narrow range.
newsitem.headline: U.S. mortgage-backeds slip, stuck in narrow range.

text.p: U.S. mortgage-backed securities drifted lower in narrow, range-bound trading on a very quiet Tuesday, traders said.
Thirty-year pass-throughs generally were flat, while discounts traded 9/32 to 10/32 lower by late afternoon.
An empty economic calendar resulted in slow-footed dealing, according to traders.
"On an average day, I probably write 50 or 60 trades," said one New York-based trader. "I've written probably 15 today."
He said he expected upcoming activity in 30-year Freddie Mac Gold 7.0 percent coupons, which were off 9/32.
"It's not beginning to look like much is going to happen until we get some economic numbers," echoed another trader.
By late Tuesday, current coupon spreads over Treasuries were modestly narrower by 2/32 to 5/32.

Ginnie Mae 30-year 7.5 percent coupons were off 9/32 at 99-12/32, yielding 109 basis points over the 10-year Treasury note. Comparable Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac paper was off 9/32 as well, at 99-09/32 and 99-15/32, respectively.
The 10-year Treasury note had slipped 11/32 at 99-17/32, yielding 6.56 percent.
